# Work Completed

## 1. Fixed Critical Data Loss Bug (Logout/Login)
**The Issue:** User reported "everything deleted" after logging out and back in. This was caused by the [DriveService](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/drive_service.dart#10-256) singleton holding onto stale state (like the old folder ID).
**The Fix:** 
- Updated `Store.initialize` in [lib/services/store.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/store.dart) to explicitly call `_driveService!.clear()` before initializing.

## 2. Implemented Offline Reliability (Local Backup)
**The Issue:** Users risked losing data if the internet cut out during save (Drive upload failed) or if the app crashed.
**The Fix:** Implemented a **Local-First Architecture** in `Store.dart`.
- **Always Save Local:** Every new/edited entry is immediately written to `journal_cache.json` on the device.
- **Instant Load:** On startup, the app loads from this local cache *first* (0 wait time).
- **Safe Sync:** Drive data is now *merged* into the local state, not replacing it. This ensures offline entries are preserved.

## 2. Fixed Google Drive Pagination (Missing Entries)
**The Issue:** The app was only loading the first 100 journal entries.
**The Fix:** Updated `DriveService.getJournalEntries` to use `nextPageToken` and loop until *all* entries are fetched.

